Modules --
A module is a file containing a code usually written by somebody else which can be import and used in our program.
There are two types of module 
1. Build in module
2. External module

PIP--
PIP is the package manager for python you can use pip to install a module on your system.

Comments --
Comments can be use used to make code more readable. Comments are used to write something which the 
programmers does not want to excute.
There are two types of comments:
1. Single line Comment
2. Multi line Comment
